Heating curve: Followed instructions for weighing w/ an air sensitive element (La), then inital melt. Si granular tends to scatter when trying to get arc to lock in, so for the steps where I would've flipped it, I instead disconnected the arc melter and pooled the scattered Si on top of the sample, flipped over, reconnected, and continued. (Initial melt, 3x flip/melt -- ~20 sec each once current is turned up, but keep on low current for a while first until everything seems to coagulate to help reduce loss.)